Premier of Gauteng David Makhura has been elected as the Co-President of the Metropolis at the World Association of Major Metropolises 12th World Congress in Montreal, Canada.ANC Gauteng Province through its provincial chairperson Paul Mashatile congratulated Makhura for being elected at World Association of Major Metropolis which is constituted of 138 major cities from across the world.Mashatile said the vote of confidence shown on Gauteng leaders by world institutions will contribute significantly to the repositioning of the province at a global level, and result in the exchange of best practices thus improving the way the province delivers services to its citizens.Speaking at the opening session of the ANC Gauteng s there-day Provincial Policy Conference held on Friday, Mashatile added that Makhura s nomination is testament that the ANC Gauteng Province has a pool of talented comrades that are able to hold their own beyond the borders of South Africa.Makhura s nomination follows that of the former Mayor for the City of Johannesburg, Parks Tau who was appointed as the President of world body United Cities and Local Governments, the umbrella body of local governments around the world in October.&#8220;The ANC Gauteng Province is proud of the recognition our deployees continue to receive from independent institutions. It is these kinds of accolades and affirmation that will reassure the residents of Gauteng Province that the confidence they have placed on the ANC-led government is not misplaced.The participation of our comrades in multinational organisations is in line with the Through the Eye of the Needle document,&#8221; he said.TNA Reporter